.<img width="600" height="363" class="wp-image-1591090" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK.jpg" alt="Gulak" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK.jpg?width=600&amp;auto_optimize=medium 600w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK-300x182.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK-58x35.jpg?width=58&amp;auto_optimize=medium 58w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK-260x157.jpg?width=260&amp;auto_optimize=medium 260w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/GULAK-200x121.jpg?width=200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 200w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> By Biodun Busari The Imo State Police Command has arrested, a 38-year-old Anosike Chimaobi, as one of the suspected killers of Ahmed Gulak, a former Political Adviser to former President Goodluck Jonathan. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, PRO, Michael Abattam disclosed this as Chimaobi was paraded, stating he is from Umuedo, Ahiazu Mbaise council area of the state. Abattam said the suspect was apprehended following a sophisticated investigation carried out by the operatives of the command. Gulak was killed on May 30, 2021, on his way to the Sam Mbakwe International Cargo Airport, Owerri. Abattam revealed that the suspect had already confessed to the crime, adding that he would be charged to court. According to the Imo Police spokesperson, Chimaobi was among the “terrorists that murdered Ahmed Gulak on May 30, 2021, along Imo State Airport Road. Being involved in the burning of Aboh Mbaise, Ahiazu Mbaise, Ezinihitte Mbaise, Ihitte-Uboma, and Obowo police stations, he confessed to being among the terrorists who attacked the onions truck at Enyiogwugwu junction Aboh Mbaise L.G.A, Imo State, on May 30. “He confessed to involvement in the attack and murder of many police officers and collection of their service rifles. He also confessed to the kidnap of one Jude Nwahiri at Eke Nguru Junction Aboh Mbaise L.G.A, Imo State, under the command of one Ebube Uche Madu aka virus, who is on the command’s wanted list.”   The Imo State Governor, Hope Uzodimma, yesterday, said that the reason he has not named those behind insecurity in Imo State was to allow  security agencies complete their  investigation.The governor disclosed this in Lagos during a media parley. In "Metro" Tension in Imo over alleged plan to assassinate PDP national Secretary In "News" In Nigeria, life has no meaning, sanctity, or value. As far as the system and its blind supporters are concerned, the murder has already been solved. Not being a “follower” of the system, this heinous crime has, to me, not been solved. That is why I ask today: Really, who… In "News"